PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
Tap-to-Earn Mobile Application with Cooldown Monetization System

1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
1.1 Product Vision
A mobile tap-to-earn application where users accumulate virtual currency (AppCoins) through tapping missions, redeemable for real Indian Rupees via UPI/PayTM. The app uses strategic cooldown timers and an integrated auto-clicker to maximize user engagement while optimizing ad revenue through controlled ad impression distribution.
1.2 Business Objectives

Achieve 80% profit margin on user payouts
Generate â‚¹500-700 in ad revenue per user who reaches â‚¹100 withdrawal threshold
Maintain premium AdMob CPM rates (â‚¹50-150) through strategic ad spacing
Achieve 60+ day average user retention through time-gating mechanics
Target 1% user conversion to withdrawal (sustainable payout model)

1.3 Target Audience

Primary: Indian users aged 18-35
Secondary Demographics: Students, gig workers, homemakers seeking supplemental income
Psychographic: Value-conscious individuals willing to invest time for monetary rewards
Device Profile: Android users (90% market share in India), mid-to-low tier devices

1.4 Core Value Proposition
Users can earn real money through unlimited tapping with integrated auto-clicker assistance, creating a perception of passive income opportunity while the cooldown system ensures sustainable revenue generation for the business.

2. PRODUCT OVERVIEW
2.1 Virtual Currency System
2.1.1 AppCoins (AC) Definition

Primary in-app virtual currency
Exchange rate: 1,000 AC = â‚¹1 INR (fixed, non-adjustable)
No expiration date on earned AC
Cannot be purchased with real money (earn-only model)
Transferable only through official withdrawal process

2.1.2 AC Earning Methods

Primary: Completing tap missions
Secondary: Daily login rewards, streak bonuses, referral rewards
Tertiary: Event participation, achievement unlocks, leaderboard prizes

2.1.3 AC Spending Options

Premium auto-clicker rentals (Bronze/Silver/Gold tiers)
Cooldown bypass purchases
Energy refills
Premium monthly passes
Special event unlocks

2.1.4 Withdrawal System

Minimum Threshold: 100,000 AC (â‚¹100)
Maximum Per Month: 200,000 AC (â‚¹200)
Processing Time: 7-10 business days
Transaction Fee: 2,000 AC (â‚¹2) deducted per withdrawal
Cooldown Period: 15 days between withdrawal requests
Payment Methods: UPI, PayTM, bank transfer (Indian accounts only)
KYC Requirements: PAN card mandatory for withdrawals above â‚¹100

2.2 User Interface Structure
2.2.1 Main Screen (Home/Tapping Interface)

Top Section:

Current AC balance (large, prominent display)
Energy bar with current/max values (100/100 format)
Active mission progress indicator (percentage + tap count)


Center Section:

Large circular tap button (60% of screen width)
Tap counter animation (numbers fly upward on each tap)
Visual feedback: Ripple effect, haptic feedback, color pulse
Auto-clicker status indicator (ON/OFF, speed display)


Bottom Section:

Mission timer display (if active)
Cooldown timer display (if active, with countdown)
Navigation bar: Home, Missions, Auto-Clicker, Leaderboard, Profile


Persistent Elements:

Banner ad strip (bottom, above navigation)
Settings icon (top right)
Notification bell (top right, shows unread count)



2.2.2 Mission Selection Screen

Layout: Vertical scrolling list of mission cards
Mission Card Components:

Mission tier badge (Quick/Medium/Premium)
Tap requirement (large number)
AC reward (highlighted in gold)
Required ads count (small text)
Cooldown duration (displayed after completion)
"Start Mission" button (or locked state if cooldown active)
Progress bar if mission partially completed


Filtering Options:

All Missions
Available Now
In Cooldown
Completed Today


Top Banner: Shows daily mission completion count and potential earnings

2.2.3 Auto-Clicker Management Screen

