Top 10 users
Prize distribution breakdown
Entry requirement status (ads watched)
Time remaining in competition


All-Time Leaders:

Total AC earned rankings
Hall of fame badges




3. COOLDOWN SYSTEM (CORE MECHANIC)
3.1 Mission Completion Cooldown
3.1.1 Cooldown Activation Trigger

Cooldown begins the instant a mission is marked "Complete"
"Complete" status triggered when: tap requirement met AND mandatory ads watched
Cooldown timer starts immediately, no grace period
User sees full-screen "Mission Complete" animation with cooldown notice

3.1.2 Cooldown Duration Tiers
Tier 1 - Quick Missions:

15-minute cooldown
Applies to missions requiring 2,000-5,000 taps
Cooldown displayed as "Next Mission: 14:37"

Tier 2 - Medium Missions:

30-minute cooldown
Applies to missions requiring 10,000-20,000 taps
Cooldown displayed as "Next Mission: 29:12"

Tier 3 - Premium Missions:

60-minute cooldown
Applies to missions requiring 50,000-100,000 taps
Cooldown displayed as "Next Mission: 59:58"

3.1.3 During Cooldown - Complete Restrictions
What Users CANNOT Do:

Start any new mission (all mission "Start" buttons greyed out)
Earn AC through tapping (taps register as zero value)
Progress on any existing mission
Claim mission rewards

What Users CAN Do:

Access all navigation screens
View missions and rewards (read-only)
Configure auto-clicker settings (but it won't tap for missions)
Watch social content (other users' achievements)
Access profile and withdrawal screens
Participate in social features (chat, team view)
View advertisements (but not for cooldown bypass yet)
Manage account settings

3.1.4 Visual Cooldown Indicators
Main Tap Button During Cooldown:

Greyed out with 50% opacity
Lock icon overlay
Tapping produces no effect (no haptic, no animation)
Text overlay: "Mission Cooldown Active"

Mission Cards During Cooldown:

Red border around locked cards
Timer countdown displayed
"Start Mission" button replaced with "Cooldown: XX:XX"
All mission details still visible (no hiding information)

Top Banner Notification:

Persistent countdown timer
Text: "Next Mission Available In: XX:XX"
Orange/yellow color scheme (indicates waiting state)

3.1.5 Cooldown Completion

Full-screen notification: "Mission Cooldown Complete!"
Confetti animation
Haptic feedback burst
Auto-navigation to Mission Selection screen
Push notification if app is in background

3.2 Cooldown Bypass Mechanisms
3.2.1 Ad-Based Bypass (Primary Method)
Option A: Partial Skip (5 minutes)

Cost: Watch 2 Rewarded Video Ads
Each ad is 30 seconds
Total time investment: ~60-75 seconds (including loading)
Reduces any cooldown by exactly 5 minutes
Can be used multiple times per cooldown
Example: 15-min cooldown â†’ watch 6 ads â†’ skip entirely

Option B: Half Skip

Cost: Watch 5 Rewarded Video Ads
Total time investment: ~3 minutes
Reduces cooldown by 50% (rounds up)
Example: 30-min cooldown â†’ 15 minutes remaining
Single use per cooldown

Option C: Full Skip

Cost: Watch 8 Rewarded Video Ads
Total time investment: ~4-5 minutes
Removes cooldown entirely
Immediately unlocks mission selection
Displays "Premium Bypass Activated" message

Bypass UI Flow:

User taps "Skip Cooldown" button on cooldown screen
Modal appears showing three options (A/B/C above)
User selects option
Ad queue begins (progress shown: "Ad 1 of 8")
After final ad, cooldown updates/removes immediately
Success confirmation screen
Return to mission selection

3.2.2 AC-Based Bypass (Secondary Method)
Quick Bypass:

Cost: 1,000 AC per 5-minute skip
No ads required
Instant application
Cost-inefficient (user awareness encouraged)
Confirmation dialog: "Spend 1,000 AC? (Worth â‚¹1)"

Full Bypass:

Cost: Varies by remaining cooldown

15-min cooldown: 3,000 AC
30-min cooldown: 6,000 AC
60-min cooldown: 12,000 AC


Confirmation dialog shows equivalent rupee value
Warns: "This delays your withdrawal by X hours of missions"
Two-step confirmation required (prevents accidental spending)

3.2.3 Premium Pass Bypass Benefits
Bronze Pass Holders (5,000 AC / 24 hours):

Can skip ONE cooldown per day for free
Free skip applies to any tier
Resets at midnight IST
"Free Skip Available" badge shown

Silver Pass Holders (12,000 AC / 24 hours):

Can skip THREE cooldowns per day for free
Each skip tracked separately
Counter display: "2/3 Free Skips Remaining"

Gold Pass Holders (25,000 AC / 7 days):

Can skip FIVE cooldowns per day for free
All cooldowns 40% shorter (automatic)

15-min â†’ 9-min
30-min â†’ 18-min
60-min â†’ 36-min


"Gold Member" badge on all screens

3.3 Ad Cooldown System (CPM Protection)
3.3.1 Interstitial Ad Cooldown
Trigger Events:

After every interstitial ad shown
After mission completion (if interstitial was last ad)
After cooldown bypass using interstitials

Cooldown Duration: 3 minutes minimum between interstitials
During Ad Cooldown:

If mission requires interstitial: Mission pauses at completion
User sees: "Ad Loading... (2:34 remaining)"
Tapping continues to register (different from mission cooldown)
Other ad types (rewarded, banner) still available
Auto-clicker continues at normal speed

Visual Indicator:

Small timer in top-right corner
Text: "Ad Ready In: 2:34"
Yellow dot indicator (not ready) â†’ Green dot (ready)

Purpose: Prevents AdMob from flagging account for spam, maintains high CPM
3.3.2 Rewarded Video Ad Cooldown
Trigger Events:

After watching any rewarded video
Marathon mode: After 3 consecutive rewarded videos

Cooldown Duration:

Single video: 5 minutes
Marathon mode (3 videos): 15 minutes

During Rewarded Ad Cooldown:

"Watch Ad" buttons greyed out
Tooltip: "Rewarded ads refresh in XX:XX"
Alternative options highlighted (AC spending, wait)
Banner and interstitial ads unaffected

Marathon Mode Details:

User can queue up to 3 rewarded videos back-to-back
After 3rd video: Longer cooldown kicks in
Notification: "Rewarded ads cooling down. Try again in 15:00"
Encourages strategic ad watching (not spam)

Purpose: Maximizes rewarded video CPM (highest revenue ads), prevents ad network penalties
3.3.3 Hourly Ad Limits (Automatic Protection)
Hard Limits:

Maximum 3 interstitial ads per hour
Maximum 6 rewarded videos per hour
No limit on banner refreshes (60/hour automatic)

When Limit Reached:

Notification: "Hourly ad limit reached. Refreshes in 42:00"
Mission rewards claimable but cooldown bypass unavailable
AC-based bypass options remain available
Premium pass skips remain available (not ad-dependent)

Limit Reset:

Rolls on 60-minute sliding window
Not hard reset at clock hour
Example: Ad watched at 2:37 PM â†’ available again at 3:37 PM

User Communication:

Counter display: "Ads Available: 2/3 interstitials, 4/6 rewarded"
Proactive notification at 1 remaining: "Last rewarded video for this hour"

3.3.4 Time-of-Day Ad Availability (Dynamic CPM Optimization)
Morning Slot (6 AM - 12 PM IST):

Ad inventory: Medium
Cooldown multiplier: 1.2x (longer cooldowns)
Example: 15-min cooldown â†’ 18 minutes
Reason: Lower advertiser demand in morning hours

Afternoon Slot (12 PM - 6 PM IST):

Ad inventory: High
Cooldown multiplier: 1.0x (standard)
Peak user activity period

Evening Slot (6 PM - 11 PM IST):

Ad inventory: Very High
Cooldown multiplier: 0.8x (shorter cooldowns)
Example: 15-min cooldown â†’ 12 minutes
Reason: Peak advertiser demand, highest CPM rates

Night Slot (11 PM - 6 AM IST):

Ad inventory: Low
Cooldown multiplier: 2.0x (double cooldowns)
Example: 15-min cooldown â†’ 30 minutes
Reason: Minimal advertiser demand, protect ad quality

User Notification:

"Evening Bonus: Cooldowns 20% shorter! (4 hours remaining)"
"Night Mode: Cooldowns longer due to low ad availability"
Encourages strategic playing during high-CPM hours


4. ENERGY SYSTEM (SECONDARY LIMITER)
4.1 Energy Mechanics
4.1.1 Energy Definition

Numerical resource required for tapping
Maximum capacity: 100 energy units (universal for all users)
Starting energy: 100 (full) for new users
Display: Progress bar format "87/100" with percentage fill

4.1.2 Energy Consumption Rate

Per Tap Cost: 0.01 energy
Calculation: 100 taps = 1 energy unit
Full Depletion: 10,000 taps exhausts 100 energy completely
Real-time Update: Energy bar decreases visibly every 100 taps

4.1.3 Energy Depletion Behavior
At 0 Energy:

Tap button becomes completely unresponsive
Message overlay: "Energy Depleted - Recharge Required"
Auto-clicker automatically stops (cannot override)
Mission progress freezes (saved, not lost)
Red pulsing border around energy bar
Three recharge options presented in modal

At Low Energy (20 or below):

Yellow warning color on energy bar
Notification: "Low Energy: 20 remaining"
Suggested action prompt appears
Auto-clicker speed reduces to 3 taps/second (efficiency loss encourages recharge)

4.1.4 Energy Regeneration (Natural)
Regeneration Rate: 1 energy unit per minute (passive)

Full recharge from 0 to 100: 100 minutes (1 hour 40 minutes)
Partial example: 50 to 100: 50 minutes
Regeneration continues when app is closed (background process)
Timer display shows: "Full Energy In: 1:23:45"

Regeneration Rules:

Starts immediately upon depletion
Cannot be paused or stopped
Continues during mission cooldowns (simultaneous)
Continues during ad cooldowns
Persists through app restarts (server-tracked)

4.1.5 Energy Refill Options (Instant)
Option 1: Ad-Based Refill

Watch 3 Rewarded Video Ads
Reward: +30 energy (instant)
Time investment: ~90 seconds
Can be used multiple times per day
No cooldown between uses (respects rewarded ad cooldown only)

Option 2: AC-Based Refill

Cost: 2,000 AC
Reward: +50 energy (instant)
Confirmation required (shows rupee equivalent: â‚¹2)
Unlimited uses (if user has AC)
Warning if user below 50,000 AC: "This delays withdrawal"

Option 3: Premium Pass Full Refill

Gold Pass exclusive benefit
Cost: 0 AC (included in pass)
Reward: Full 100 energy (instant)
Limit: Once per day
Resets at midnight IST
"Daily Full Refill Available" badge shown

4.1.6 Energy Display and Notifications
Main Screen Display:

Horizontal bar below AC balance
Color coding:

Green: 70-100 energy
Yellow: 21-69 energy
Red: 0-20 energy


Numerical display: "87/100 Energy"
Percentage indicator: Small text below bar

Low Energy Notifications:

At 20 energy: In-app banner "Low Energy Warning"
At 5 energy: Modal popup "Energy Almost Depleted"
At 0 energy: Full-screen "Energy Empty" with refill options

Background Energy Full Notification:

Push notification when energy reaches 100
Message: "Energy Recharged! Resume your missions now!"
Only sent if user away for 100+ minutes

4.2 Energy and Auto-Clicker Integration
4.2.1 Auto-Clicker Energy Consumption

Consumes energy at normal rate (0.01 per tap)
No discount or efficiency bonus
Example: 10 taps/second = 0.1 energy/second = 1 energy per 10 seconds

4.2.2 Auto-Clicker Behavior at Low Energy
At 20 Energy:

Speed reduces to 50% (from 10 taps/sec â†’ 5 taps/sec)
Notification: "Auto-Clicker Slowed: Low Energy"
Flashing energy bar visual

At 5 Energy:

Speed reduces to 25% (from 10 taps/sec â†’ 2.5 taps/sec)
Notification: "Auto-Clicker Critical: Recharge Soon"
Red pulsing animation on auto-clicker icon

At 0 Energy:

Auto-clicker stops completely
Cannot be restarted until energy above 10
Modal: "Auto-Clicker Paused: No Energy"
Refill options prominently displayed

4.2.3 Premium Pass Energy Efficiency
Gold Pass Benefit:

Energy consumption reduced by 30%
Calculation: 0.01 energy per tap â†’ 0.007 energy per tap
Effective capacity: 100 energy = 14,285 taps (vs standard 10,000)
Badge on energy bar: "30% More Efficient"
Encourages Gold Pass purchases for long-grind users


5. MISSION SYSTEM
5.1 Mission Structure
5.1.1 Mission Tiers
TIER 1: QUICK MISSIONS
Mission 1A:

Tap Requirement: 2,000 taps
AC Reward: 40 AC
Mandatory Ads: 1 Interstitial (after completion)
Energy Cost: 20 energy
Cooldown: 15 minutes
Estimated Time: 5-8 minutes (manual), 3-4 minutes (auto-clicker)

Mission 1B:

Tap Requirement: 5,000 taps
AC Reward: 100 AC
Mandatory Ads: 2 Interstitials (1 at 50%, 1 at 100%)
Energy Cost: 50 energy
Cooldown: 15 minutes
Estimated Time: 12-15 minutes (manual), 8-10 minutes (auto-clicker)

TIER 2: MEDIUM MISSIONS
Mission 2A:

Tap Requirement: 10,000 taps
AC Reward: 250 AC
Mandatory Ads: 1 Rewarded Video + 2 Interstitials (at 33%, 66%, 100%)
Energy Cost: 100 energy (full bar)
Cooldown: 30 minutes
Estimated Time: 25-30 minutes (manual), 15-20 minutes (auto-clicker)

Mission 2B:

Tap Requirement: 20,000 taps
AC Reward: 600 AC
Mandatory Ads: 2 Rewarded Videos + 3 Interstitials (at 25%, 50%, 75%, 100%, final)
Energy Cost: 200 energy (requires 1 refill mid-mission)
Cooldown: 30 minutes
Estimated Time: 45-60 minutes (manual), 30-40 minutes (auto-clicker)

TIER 3: PREMIUM MISSIONS
Mission 3A:

Tap Requirement: 50,000 taps
AC Reward: 1,500 AC
Mandatory Ads: 3 Rewarded Videos + 5 Interstitials (spread across progress)
Energy Cost: 500 energy (requires 4 refills)
Cooldown: 60 minutes
Estimated Time: 2-2.5 hours (manual), 1-1.5 hours (auto-clicker)

Mission 3B:

Tap Requirement: 100,000 taps
AC Reward: 3,500 AC
Mandatory Ads: 5 Rewarded Videos + 8 Interstitials
Energy Cost: 1,000 energy (requires 9 refills)
Cooldown: 60 minutes
Estimated Time: 4-5 hours (manual), 2.5-3 hours (auto-clicker)

5.1.2 Mission Progression Checkpoints
Ad Trigger Points:
Each mission has predetermined tap count thresholds where ads trigger:
Example (Mission 2A - 10,000 taps):

Checkpoint 1: 3,300 taps â†’ Interstitial Ad
Checkpoint 2: 6,600 taps â†’ Rewarded Video
Checkpoint 3: 10,000 taps â†’ Interstitial Ad

Checkpoint Behavior:

User reaches checkpoint tap count
Tapping immediately pauses (auto-clicker stops)
Ad plays automatically (no skip option)
After ad completion: Ad cooldown begins (if applicable)
Mission resumes after ad cooldown expires
Progress saved (if user exits, continues from checkpoint)

Visual Checkpoint Indicators:

Progress bar shows vertical markers at checkpoint positions
Text: "Next Ad At: 3,300 taps"
Changes color as approaching checkpoint (green â†’ yellow â†’ red)

5.1.3 Mission Completion Requirements
All Conditions Must Be Met:

Exact tap count reached (not exceeded, exact match)
All mandatory ads watched completely
All ad cooldowns cleared (no pending ad cooldowns)
User must claim reward (active action required)

Claim Reward Flow:

Mission shows "Complete" status
Tap count stops incrementing
"Claim Reward" button appears (large, centered)
User taps button
Animation: Coins fly into AC balance counter
Final confirmation: "+600 AC Earned!"
Mission cooldown timer starts immediately

If User Doesn't Claim:

Reward remains claimable indefinitely
Cannot start new missions until claimed
Reminder notification every 5 minutes

5.1.4 Mission Abandonment
User Can Abandon Mission:

"Abandon Mission" button in mission details
Confirmation dialog: "Lose all progress? (XX taps, XX ads watched)"
If confirmed:

All taps lost (no partial credit)
Ads watched not refunded (ad view counts remain)
Energy consumed not refunded
No cooldown applied
Can immediately start new mission



Automatic Abandonment:

If user doesn't interact with app for 48 hours during active mission
Progress saved for 48 hours, then auto-abandoned
Push notification at 36 hours: "Complete your mission or lose progress!"

5.2 Mission Availability and Rotation
5.2.1 Daily Mission Limits
No daily mission completion limits - users can complete unlimited missions

Only limited by cooldowns and energy
Encourages marathon sessions

5.2.2 Mission Unlocking
Tier Unlocking System:

Tier 1 (Quick): Available immediately for new users
Tier 2 (Medium): Unlocks after completing 5 Tier 1 missions
Tier 3 (Premium): Unlocks after completing 10 Tier 2 missions

Unlock Notifications:

"Achievement Unlocked: Medium Missions Available!"
Confetti animation
Tutorial tooltip explaining new tier

5.2.3 Special Missions (Time-Limited)
Daily Challenge Mission:

Available once per day (resets midnight IST)
Tap Requirement: 30,000 taps
AC Reward: 2,000 AC (2x standard rate)
Mandatory Ads: 10 Rewarded Videos + 6 Interstitials
Energy Cost: 300 energy
Cooldown: None (only 1 attempt per day)
Time Limit: Must complete within 24 hours of starting

Weekend Bonus Missions (Saturday-Sunday only):

Higher AC rewards (1.5x multiplier)
Same tap requirements
Same ads required
Shorter cooldowns (50% reduction)
Special badge on completion

Event Missions (Monthly):

Announced 7 days in advance
Mega rewards (5,000-10,000 AC)
Extreme tap requirements (200,000+ taps)
Entry fee: Watch 20 ads upfront
Time limit: 7 days to complete
Leaderboard for fastest completion


6. AUTO-CLICKER SYSTEM
6.1 Free Auto-Clicker
6.1.1 Basic Specifications

Speed: 5 taps per second (300 taps per minute)
Cost: Free (permanently available to all users)
Toggle: ON/OFF switch on main screen and auto-clicker screen
Energy Consumption: Standard rate (0.05 energy per second)
Visual Indicator: Pulsing circle around tap button when active

6.1.2 Free Auto-Clicker Limitations
Pauses Automatically When:

Energy reaches 0 (cannot override)
Mission cooldown begins (cannot be used during cooldown)
Ad cooldown active (pauses for 3-5 minutes)
Checkpoint ad triggers (stops until ad completes + cooldown)
User manually pauses (tap button toggles it off)

Pause Display:

Greyed out tap button
Pause icon overlay
Reason text: "Paused: Ad Cooldown (2:34 remaining)"
Auto-resumes when pause reason clears

6.1.3 Free Auto-Clicker Benefits

Hands-free tapping (user can multitask)
Consistent tap rate (no fatigue)
Works with screen off (background mode after first minute)
Progress saved during interruptions

6.1.4 Free Auto-Clicker Usage Analytics

Tracks total auto-clicker time used
Displays on profile: "Auto-Clicker: 24h 35m"
Achievement unlocks at milestones (10h, 50h, 100h)

