7. ADVERTISEMENT INTEGRATION
7.1 Ad Types and Placement
7.1.1 Banner Ads
Placement: Bottom of screen, above navigation bar
Specifications:

Size: 320x50 pixels (standard mobile banner)
Always visible on: Home, Mission Selection, Auto-Clicker, Leaderboard screens
Hidden during: Active ad viewing, mission completion animations
Refresh Rate: Every 60 seconds (automatic)
Click-through: Opens in-app browser

Revenue Expectations:

CPM: â‚¹20-30 (average â‚¹25)
Per user per day: 120-180 impressions (2-3 hours active usage)
Daily revenue per user: â‚¹3-4.5 from banners alone

User Experience:

Non-intrusive (doesn't block content)
Can be scrolled past on long screens
No accidental click protection (placement away from tap button)

7.1.2 Interstitial Ads
Trigger Points:

Mission checkpoint reaches (predetermined taps)
Mission completion (before reward claim)
Every 500 taps during continuous tapping (if no active mission)
App resume after 5+ minutes away

Specifications:

Full-screen takeover
Duration: 5-15 seconds (static) or 30 seconds (video)
Skip button: After 5 seconds (static) or non-skippable (video)
Close button: Prominent X in top-right corner
Loading time: 2-4 seconds (cached when possible)

Revenue Expectations:

CPM: â‚¹40-60 (average â‚¹50)
Per user per day: 8-15 impressions
Daily revenue per user: â‚¹4-7.5 from interstitials

User Experience:

Warning before display: "Loading reward..." (2 seconds)
Progress indicator: "Ad 1 of 3" during checkpoint sequences
Cannot be skipped prematurely
Must watch to completion

7.1.3 Rewarded Video Ads
Trigger Points (User-Initiated):

Cooldown bypass option selected
Energy refill option selected
Daily spin wheel activation
Leaderboard entry requirement
Bonus AC offers ("Watch ad for +200 AC")
Mission completion reward doubler

Specifications:

Full-screen video (vertical or horizontal)
Duration: 15-30 seconds (typically 30)
Non-skippable (must watch to completion)
Close button: Appears only after completion
Loading screen: "Preparing your reward..."

Revenue Expectations:

CPM: â‚¹100-150 (average â‚¹120)
Per user per day: 10-25 impressions (highly engaged users)
Daily revenue per user: â‚¹12-30 from rewarded videos

User Experience:

Clear benefit statement before watching: "Watch 30-sec ad â†’ Get 30 energy"
Progress bar during video: "15 seconds remaining"
Reward confirmation after completion: "30 Energy Added!"
Cannot close app during video (progress lost if closed)

Verification System:

Server-side callback from AdMob
Reward only granted after verification
If verification fails: "Ad incomplete - please try again"
Prevents fraud/ad-blockers

7.2 Ad Frequency Management
7.2.1 Daily Ad Impression Targets
Per Active User:

Banner impressions: 120-180
Interstitial impressions: 10-15
Rewarded video impressions: 15-25
Total revenue target: â‚¹25-40 per day

7.2.2 Ad Cooldown Enforcement (Detailed)
Interstitial Cooldown:

3 minutes minimum between impressions
Tracked server-side (cannot be bypassed)
If triggered during cooldown:

Mission pauses at checkpoint
Message: "Ad ready in 1:45 - Mission will resume"
User can wait or spend AC to skip wait



Rewarded Video Cooldown:

5 minutes minimum between single videos
15 minutes after "marathon" (3 consecutive videos)
Marathon counter resets after 15 minutes of no videos watched
Display: "Rewarded Ads: 2/3 before cooldown"

Hourly Caps:

3 interstitials per rolling hour
6 rewarded videos per rolling hour
If cap reached:

All ad buttons greyed out
Tooltip: "Hourly ad limit reached. Resets at 3:45 PM"
Alternative options highlighted (AC spending)



Dynamic Adjustment:

If ad fill rate low (< 70%): Increase cooldown by 50%
If ad fill rate high (> 90%): Standard cooldowns
Protects user experience and CPM rates

7.2.3 Time-of-Day Ad Availability
Peak Hours (6 PM - 11 PM IST):

Standard cooldowns
All ad types readily available
Highest CPM rates (â‚¹50-150)
Notification: "Peak Hours: Best time to earn!"

Off-Peak Hours (6 AM - 6 PM IST):

Cooldowns increased by 20%
Slightly lower fill rates
Moderate CPM rates (â‚¹40-120)

Late Night (11 PM - 6 AM IST):

Cooldowns doubled (protection mode)
Lower fill rates (60-80%)
Lower CPM rates (â‚¹30-80)
Warning: "Late night - ad availability limited"

User Notification:

"Best earning hours: 6 PM - 11 PM"
Push notification at 5:45 PM: "Peak ad hours starting soon!"

7.3 Ad Revenue Optimization Strategies
7.3.1 Rewarded Video Prioritization
Why Rewarded Videos Are Key:

Highest CPM (â‚¹120 vs â‚¹50 for interstitials)
User-initiated (better engagement)
Higher completion rates (95%+ vs 70% for interstitials)

How to Maximize:

Make cooldown bypass require rewarded videos (not just interstitials)
Energy refills exclusively through rewarded videos
Daily bonuses require rewarded video to claim
Leaderboard entry requires rewarded videos
Mission reward doublers through rewarded videos

Target: 60% of total ad revenue from rewarded videos
7.3.2 Ad Mediation Strategy
Primary Ad Network: Google AdMob
Backup Networks (waterfall):

Facebook Audience Network (if AdMob fails)
Unity Ads (second backup)
AppLovin (final backup)

Waterfall Logic:

Request ad from AdMob first
If no fill within 3 seconds â†’ Request from Facebook
If no fill within 3 seconds â†’ Request from Unity
If no fill â†’ Display "Ad unavailable" message

Purpose: Maximize fill rate (target 95%+) and CPM
7.3.3 Ad Quality Filtering
Blocked Categories:

Gambling/Betting apps
Adult content
Misinformation/fake news
Violent games (graphic content)
Cryptocurrency/trading apps (user protection)

Why: Maintain app reputation, protect users, comply with Google Play policies
7.3.4 A/B Testing Plans
Test Variables:

Ad cooldown lengths (2 min vs 3 min vs 4 min)
Rewarded video reward amounts (30 vs 40 vs 50 energy)
Interstitial frequency (every 500 vs 750 taps)
Mission checkpoint ad placement (early vs late)

Success Metrics:

Revenue per daily active user (ARPDAU)
Ad impression per user per day
User retention rate (Day 7, Day 30)
Withdrawal completion rate


